# Digital Lock-In Girlfriend 👩‍❤️‍💋‍👨

A web app that simulates a FaceTime call with a virtual girlfriend who yells at you for doom scrolling. Perfect for staying focused during study sessions!

![Preview](https://img.shields.io/badge/Platform-Web-blue) ![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-MVP-green)

## Features

- 📹 **Video Call Interface** - Anime-style girlfriend character that reacts to your presence
- 👀 **Face Detection** - Uses your webcam to monitor if you're looking at the screen
- ⏱️ **Doom Scroll Timer** - Counts how long you've been staring (default: 10 seconds)
- 🔥 **Scolding System** - Voice scolds you when you've been looking too long
- 📴 **PWA Support** - Works offline after first load
- 💕 **Cute Character** - Pure CSS animated anime girlfriend with expressions

## How It Works

1. Click **"Start Call"** to begin the session
2. Grant camera permission when prompted
3. The girlfriend will watch you through the camera
4. If you stare at the screen for more than 10 seconds...
5. She'll yell at you to get back to work!
6. Look away to reset the timer

## Tech Stack

- **HTML5/CSS3/JavaScript** - Vanilla web technologies
- **face-api.js** - Face detection in the browser
- **Web Speech API** - Text-to-speech for scolding
- **Service Worker** - PWA offline capabilities

## Running Locally

1. Clone this repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/digital-lock-in-girlfriend.git
cd digital-lock-in-girlfriend
```

2. Start a local server (required for camera access):
```bash
# Using Python
python -m http.server 8000

# Using Node.js
npx serve .

# Using PHP
php -S localhost:8000
```

3. Open http://localhost:8000 in your browser

## Hosting on GitHub Pages

1. Create a new repository on GitHub
2. Push your code:
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/repo-name.git
git push -u origin main
```

3. Go to Settings → Pages → Deploy from main branch

4. Your app will be live at `https://yourusername.github.io/repo-name/`

## Permissions Required

- **Camera** - For face detection to monitor if you're looking at the screen
- **Microphone** - Not required (voice uses Web Speech API)

## Browser Compatibility

- Chrome/Edge 80+ (recommended)
- Firefox 75+
- Safari 14+ (may have limited face detection support)

## Customization

### Changing Scold Threshold
Edit [`script.js`](script.js) and change:
```javascript
const CONFIG = {
    SCOLD_THRESHOLD: 10,  // seconds before scolding
    SCOLD_COOLDOWN: 15,   // seconds between scolds
};
```

### Changing Scold Messages
Edit [`animations.js`](animations.js):
```javascript
scoldMessages: [
    "Hey! Get back to work!",
    "Stop scrolling!",
    // Add your own messages
]
```

## Known Limitations

- Face detection requires good lighting
- Works best on laptop with webcam
- Some browsers may block camera in iframes (use direct URL)

